lumol (https://github.com/lumol-org/lumol)
------------------------------------------

The long-range electrostatics and Monte Carlo algorithms in the
`valenx-md` crate — specifically the Ewald / Wolf damped-shifted-force
electrostatics and the Metropolis Monte Carlo move/acceptance scheme —
were reimplemented in Rust with reference to lumol, an extensible
molecular-simulation engine. No lumol source code is vendored; the
implementations are independent Rust written against the same standard
methods (Ewald 1921; Wolf et al. 1999; Fennell & Gezelter 2006;
Metropolis et al. 1953) and cross-checked against published ground truth
(e.g. the NaCl Madelung constant). lumol is credited here per its
BSD-3-Clause license.

