molchanica (https://github.com/David-OConnor/molchanica)
--------------------------------------------------------

The richer molecular-viewer representations in the `valenx-app` crate's
`molviz` module — the set of representation modes (ball-and-stick /
sticks / spacefill / cartoon-ribbon / molecular surface) and the
union-of-balls-to-marching-cubes approach for the molecular surface —
were implemented with reference to molchanica, an open-source molecular
viewer/editor by David O'Connor. No molchanica source code is vendored or
copied; the geometry generators are an independent Rust reimplementation
written against the standard published algorithms — table-driven marching
cubes (Lorensen & Cline, "Marching Cubes: A High Resolution 3D Surface
Construction Algorithm," SIGGRAPH 1987), the Catmull-Rom spline (Catmull &
Rom, "A class of local interpolating splines," 1974) for the backbone
ribbon, and the Kabsch-Sander DSSP secondary-structure assignment
(`valenx-biostruct`) that drives the cartoon tube width. molchanica is
credited here per its MIT license.

